Traveling through or driving 🚘🚗 in the city can be a bit of a headache if most of the day will be spent here running 🏃💨💨 errands or just working. I was undecided about what to have for brunch, and a colleague of mine referred me to Da Vinci Pizzeria Restaurant 🍴. Upon entering the premise, I was greeted by one of the Pizzeria Staff. I ordered two slices of plain pizza 🍕 and a Welch Soda. I'd suggest that Wi-Fi Internet access be made available to customers as that would attract a more trendy crowd. 😁 I don't see why a pizzeria can't have FREE wireless-Internet for its customers. 🤔  - Noticeable from traffic on Water St, - No FREE parking for customers, - For city street parking: ParkNYC app 📲, - For parking garages: SpotHero app 📲, - FREE public restroom 🚻 for customers, - Entrance is not wheelchair ♿ accessible,  - Clean environment, 🤝 - Table seating available, - Pizza 🍕 is crispy and tasty, 👍 - Moderately inexpensive menu, 🤝 - Delivery via the Seamless app 📲, 🤝 - Eat-in and takeout allowed, 🤝 - Sanitary Inspection Grade: A, 👍 - No Wi-Fi hotspot, 👎  I'd recommend having a slice 🍕 🍕 of pizza at Da Vinci Pizzeria because of its professionalism, customer service and scrumptious crispy pizza 🍕. Planning ahead of time for short- and long-term parking is crucial when coming to Manhattan. And knowing where to park while taking care of business can be less frustrating and stressful. Public transportation is much better.

This is one of many more-or-less identical pizza slice places in New York. But because it was very close to where I was working once, I went here dozens of times or more, and I like it. The pizza is good, and they have quite a few varieties of both regular and square pizza. I’d usually get a couple of slices for lunch. The plain cheese and margherita slices are pretty good, and the grandma pizza squares are very good. Just thinking about it makes me hungry for more pizza!  The staff are very helpful and, like it says on the door, they have air conditioning!
Great pizza. They are always fast and friendly. One of my favorite spots for lunch.

The music at our first jazz brunch at the Blue Note was fantastic! Kyoko Oyobe provided the perfect Sunday morning soundtrack. I loved her music and her vibe and her band. Now, the Blue Note is probably not exactly sought out for its menu as opposed to its music, but the food was good, and our server was really helpful about making a substitution to accommodate my vegetarianism in terms of a dish I wanted, and the home fries were like a cross between hash browns and mashed potatoes, which was amazing. Absolutely worth going.

The BEST pizza and rice balls in New York. Authentic Italian quality and fairly priced. This is a multi-generational family run restaurant and their food is definitely Made With Love! You can taste the difference.

So good we went there twice during our 4 day trip! Service is great, the people are friendly, and the pizza is terrific. Very cute little place, nothing fancy, but with great food and great service, they don't really need anything more.

Is it fancy? Nah. Does it looks like it should be? Nah! Good stuff. I had their pizza rolls -- one veggie (primarily spinach and garlic) and the other pepperoni. The cheese was far superior to the mozzarella crap-o-la you usually find at low-grade pizza stops. So instant upgrade in my book. Quick, fast, and pleasant service. Thumbs up and belly full!
